The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, August 25, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The swap ratio for the merger of Gestetner India Ltd with Ricoh India Ltd has been set at one is to six. This means that six shares in Ricoh India will be exchanged for one share of Gestetner India. The companies will soon approach the high courts at Mumbai and Calcutta to seek their sanction of the swap ratio. The merger was announced at a joint press conference here today by the two companies.																								 Calcutta, Aug. 24: Visakhapatnam steel plant of Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Ltd (RINL) today cut prices of all its products by Rs 1,000 in line with price cuts by other steel producers.																								 London, Aug. 24: Scotch malt whisky distiller Glenmorangie Plc is seeking offers for the company and is in preliminary talks with a number of potentially interested parties, the company said.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 24: Sebi has found that promoter of the Global Trust Bank, Ramesh Gelli and eight other entities, including two FIIs, had offloaded GTB scrips even after the Centre announced a moratorium on the bank.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 24: The government will build strategic storage of crude of five million tonnes capacity to ensure energy security.
